Progress over everything.

Grateful for another trip around the sun. What a life🙏🏼🌍💕 
Here’s to chapter 31.

Can you move like Courtnaé Paul?

If the answer is YES, the Olympic #StreetChallenge is for you. Send in a 30-second video of your best breaking moves for the chance to win a once-in-a-lifetime Olympic experience.

Visit the link in our bio to sign up.

#LetsMove

Anyone who knows me, knows that I’m a very positive person and often don’t entertain the BS that I encounter daily, but what you’re not gonna do is get comfortable disrespecting me.

The amount of time, effort, sacrifice and personal funds I pump into bettering myself and representing my country / continent, my work rate speaks for itself. No hand outs, just work. 

I generally only see this in SA, where dancers want to pull each other down instead of supporting, keeping quiet, or letting your skill speak.

This post with the Olympics is exactly that, for people to enter and SHOW UP - not talking smack and hoping for opportunities. When they land on our soil, you choose to scoff instead.

I love what I do, and I create opportunities doing it. 
Also remember that there might be better singers than Beyoncé… yet?

Anyway, you got your 2 seconds.
As always, onto the next 😎🚀

Inhale, 
Exhale, 
Take a chance ❤️‍🔥
